1
00:00:31,498 --> 00:00:34,171
[FROGS CROAKING]

2
00:00:39,498 --> 00:00:42,854
[SINGING]

3
00:02:08,698 --> 00:02:11,690
[DOOR SQUEAKS]

4
00:02:13,218 --> 00:02:16,096
[SINGING
"MICHAEL, ROW THE BOAT ASHORE"]

5
00:02:34,058 --> 00:02:35,093
WOMAN:
Where's Jay?

6
00:02:38,938 --> 00:02:42,487
How long were those potatoes
under the fire? How'd you do that?

7
00:02:42,738 --> 00:02:46,890
[SINGING "TOM DOOLEY"]

8
00:02:53,018 --> 00:02:55,976
- Somebody will see!
BARRY: No way.

9
00:03:01,498 --> 00:03:04,570
- Does Maryann kiss as good as I do?
- How would I know?

10
00:03:04,738 --> 00:03:06,774
- Oh, you.
- Come on.

11
00:03:18,458 --> 00:03:22,770
- You said we were special.
- I meant everything.

12
00:03:49,378 --> 00:03:51,812
[CLAUDETTE GIGGLING]

13
00:04:06,698 --> 00:04:10,327
CLAUDETTE: That's not allowed.
BARRY: Come on.

14
00:04:15,458 --> 00:04:19,895
Come on.
A man is not made out of stone.

15
00:04:22,378 --> 00:04:23,367
[FLOOR SQUEAKING]

16
00:04:23,538 --> 00:04:25,574
CLAUDETTE:
Somebody's there!

17
00:04:34,818 --> 00:04:37,013
We weren't doing anything.
We were just messing a...

18
00:04:37,178 --> 00:04:38,657
[CLAUDETTE SCREAMS]

19
00:04:48,418 --> 00:04:50,568
Please, don't!

20
00:05:00,898 --> 00:05:03,173
No!

21
00:06:36,178 --> 00:06:38,089
[CHURCH BELL RINGING]

22
00:06:38,258 --> 00:06:40,328
[DOG BARKING]

23
00:07:12,098 --> 00:07:15,295
Hi, girl. Excuse me! Hi, boy.

24
00:07:15,458 --> 00:07:18,256
You speak English?
How far is it to Camp Crystal Lake?

25
00:07:18,418 --> 00:07:19,453
[DOG WHINES]

26
00:07:19,618 --> 00:07:23,691
That far?
Okey-dokey. See you later.

27
00:07:32,258 --> 00:07:36,217
MAN OVER RADIO:
<i>It's 7:01 on Friday the 13th of June.</i>

28
00:07:36,378 --> 00:07:40,894
<i>This is Big Dave and it's time for you</i>
<i>lazybones to get out of bed.</i>

29
00:07:41,058 --> 00:07:44,448
<i>It's black-cat day in Crystal Lake.</i>

30
00:07:44,618 --> 00:07:46,654
[MUSIC PLAYS OVER RADIO]

31
00:07:51,338 --> 00:07:54,296
I must have seen that <i>Kojak</i> 82 times.

32
00:07:54,458 --> 00:07:57,336
Excuse me. How far
is Camp Crystal Lake from here?

33
00:08:03,338 --> 00:08:06,216
What is it, Enos? About 20 miles?

34
00:08:06,378 --> 00:08:08,255
- About that.
- Camp Blood?

35
00:08:08,418 --> 00:08:12,206
- They're opening that place again?
ENOS: Lots of luck.

36
00:08:12,378 --> 00:08:15,370
- Can I get a bus or something?
WOMAN: Not likely.

37
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:20,606
You going out to the crossroads, Enos?
What about a lift? That'd be halfway.

38
00:08:20,778 --> 00:08:24,134
No sweat, Trudy.
Okay, kid, let's move it.

39
00:08:25,098 --> 00:08:28,693
- Name's Annie.
- All right, Annie, let's go.

40
00:08:35,698 --> 00:08:37,893
All the girls up there
gonna look as good as you?

41
00:08:38,058 --> 00:08:40,014
I don't know.

42
00:08:40,418 --> 00:08:44,889
- You're going to Camp Blood, ain't you?
- Goddamn it, Ralph, get out of here!

43
00:08:45,058 --> 00:08:48,050
- Leave people alone!
- You'll never come back!

44
00:08:48,258 --> 00:08:50,214
Oh, shut up, Ralph!

45
00:08:51,138 --> 00:08:54,335
It's got a death curse!

46
00:08:56,258 --> 00:08:59,091
He's a real prophet of doom, ain't he?

47
00:09:00,018 --> 00:09:01,007
Climb up, miss.

48
00:09:19,378 --> 00:09:23,690
He's causing problems enough
for your boss with all that talk.

49
00:09:25,018 --> 00:09:27,657
Goddamn nuisance.

50
00:09:50,738 --> 00:09:53,616
- He tell you anything?
- Who?

51
00:09:53,778 --> 00:09:56,292
Your boss. Steve Christy.

52
00:09:56,458 --> 00:10:00,133
I'll be cooking for 50 kids and 10 staff.

53
00:10:00,298 --> 00:10:05,577
- Campers are mostly inner-city children.
- No, I mean about what happened.

54
00:10:08,258 --> 00:10:10,135
No.

55
00:10:14,778 --> 00:10:17,736
Come on. There's something
you're not telling me.

56
00:10:19,938 --> 00:10:24,966
- Quit. Quit now.
- Quit? Why would I want to quit?

57
00:10:25,858 --> 00:10:28,133
Camp Crystal Lake is jinxed!

58
00:10:28,338 --> 00:10:32,570
Terrific. Not you too. You sound
like your crazy friend back there.

59
00:10:32,738 --> 00:10:37,448
Well, maybe. Did Christy tell you about
the two kids murdered in '58?

60
00:10:38,218 --> 00:10:42,928
Boy drowning in '57? A bunch of fires?

61
00:10:43,098 --> 00:10:45,168
Nobody knows who did any of them.

62
00:10:45,338 --> 00:10:49,854
In 1962, they were going to open up.
The water was bad.

63
00:10:50,018 --> 00:10:53,090
Christy will end up like his folks:
Crazy and broke.

64
00:10:53,258 --> 00:10:57,968
He's been up there a year fixing up that
place. Must have dropped $25,000.

65
00:10:58,138 --> 00:11:01,847
And for what? Ask anybody.

66
00:11:02,498 --> 00:11:05,888
- Quit!
- I can't.

67
00:11:06,538 --> 00:11:09,610
Dumb kids. Know-it-alls.

68
00:11:09,778 --> 00:11:13,168
Just like my nieces. Heads full of rocks.

69
00:11:13,378 --> 00:11:18,850
- You're an American original.
- I'm an American original.

70
00:11:19,018 --> 00:11:24,046
- Dumb kid.
- At least I'm not afraid of ghosts.

71
00:11:24,778 --> 00:11:26,177
[CHUCKLES]

72
00:11:44,138 --> 00:11:47,687
- Take care of yourself.
- No sweat. Thanks for the lift.

73
00:12:08,018 --> 00:12:10,691
[BLUEGRASS MUSIC PLAYS]

74
00:12:19,538 --> 00:12:23,417
Hey, Marcie. You really think
there'll be other gorgeous women...

75
00:12:23,578 --> 00:12:26,536
...at Camp Crystal Lake besides yourself?

76
00:12:26,698 --> 00:12:28,689
Is sex all you ever think about, Ned?

77
00:12:28,858 --> 00:12:30,849
- Hey, no. No. Absolutely not.
- Ha.

78
00:12:31,018 --> 00:12:33,930
NED: Sometimes I just think about
kissing women.

79
00:12:42,898 --> 00:12:45,617
[CHUCKLING]

80
00:13:15,938 --> 00:13:18,133
[TRUCK APPROACHES]

81
00:13:33,538 --> 00:13:36,928
STEVE: You wanna give me a hand here?
NED: Sure.

82
00:13:38,178 --> 00:13:40,646
Alice! I wanna get this tree stump out.

83
00:13:40,818 --> 00:13:44,254
Get on this side, you pull
on that side. Alice!

84
00:13:44,418 --> 00:13:45,646
Coming.

85
00:13:49,258 --> 00:13:52,136
- That's great. I'm Steve Christy.
- Jack.

86
00:13:52,298 --> 00:13:53,811
MARCIE: Marcie.
NED: Ned Rubinstein.

87
00:13:53,978 --> 00:13:55,969
STEVE: Welcome to Camp Crystal Lake.
- Thanks.

88
00:13:56,138 --> 00:13:58,857
STEVE: This is Alice.
- Hi. Steve, Cabin B is all ready.

89
00:13:59,018 --> 00:14:03,409
STEVE: Is Bill cleaning the boathouse?
- Haven't seen him in half an hour.

90
00:14:03,618 --> 00:14:05,973
I wanted him to start painting. Brenda?

91
00:14:06,138 --> 00:14:10,575
- Setting up the archery range.
- I'd rather she paint. Come on. Let's go.

92
00:14:10,738 --> 00:14:12,694
I thought we had two weeks.

93
00:14:12,858 --> 00:14:15,930
Come on. I'll show you
where you can get changed.

94
00:14:24,178 --> 00:14:28,137
- Here, let me give you a hand with that.
ALICE: Thank you.

95
00:14:36,858 --> 00:14:38,576
You got it?

96
00:14:58,658 --> 00:15:00,933
You draw very well.

97
00:15:02,178 --> 00:15:05,614
Thanks. I wish I had more time to do it.

98
00:15:05,778 --> 00:15:07,370
Oh, dummy.

99
00:15:08,418 --> 00:15:11,728
- When did you do this?
- Last night.

100
00:15:13,058 --> 00:15:16,846
- Do I really look like that?
- You did last night.

101
00:15:22,058 --> 00:15:24,333
STEVE:
You're very talented.

102
00:15:26,378 --> 00:15:28,573
You're very pretty.

103
00:15:30,538 --> 00:15:33,257
This really isn't your cup of tea, is it?

104
00:15:34,018 --> 00:15:36,134
Any particular reason?

105
00:15:36,298 --> 00:15:40,291
It's just a problem I have.
It's nothing personal.

106
00:15:42,818 --> 00:15:45,457
- You wanna leave?
- I don't know. I may have to...

107
00:15:45,618 --> 00:15:48,496
...go back to California
to straighten something out.

108
00:15:51,498 --> 00:15:54,695
Come on. Give me another chance.

109
00:15:55,578 --> 00:15:58,854
Stay a week.
Help get the place ready.

110
00:15:59,298 --> 00:16:04,213
By Friday, if you're not happy,
I'll put you on the bus myself.

111
00:16:05,298 --> 00:16:09,257
All right. Friday. I'll give it a week.

112
00:16:15,578 --> 00:16:17,569
Thanks, Alice.

113
00:16:31,458 --> 00:16:34,530
ALICE: Bill? Steve wants to know
if we need more paint.

114
00:16:34,698 --> 00:16:38,134
- Paint's all right. Need more thinner.
- Okay.

115
00:16:38,298 --> 00:16:43,088
- Alice. Did the others show up?
- Yeah, everybody except that girl Annie.

116
00:16:43,298 --> 00:16:48,053
- Think you're gonna last all summer?
- I don't know if I'm gonna last all week.

117
00:16:48,218 --> 00:16:50,686
- I'll tell Steve about the thinner.
- Fine.

118
00:17:05,098 --> 00:17:07,976
JACK: You want it listed separately?
- Right.

119
00:17:08,138 --> 00:17:10,891
Brenda, I want you to
finish the archery range.

120
00:17:11,058 --> 00:17:14,573
If Annie gets here, get her started
in the kitchen. Do your best.

121
00:17:14,738 --> 00:17:17,457
- All right.
- I'll be back sometime after lunch.

122
00:17:17,618 --> 00:17:22,169
It's supposed to rain like hell,
so get as much done as possible.

123
00:17:24,538 --> 00:17:26,210
Bye.

124
00:17:27,658 --> 00:17:32,288
He neglected to mention that downtown
they call this place "Camp Blood."

125
00:17:32,458 --> 00:17:36,974
Next there'll be snakes in the
outhouse and crocodiles in the lake.

126
00:17:37,138 --> 00:17:40,096
NED:
No, the crocodiles are in the cabins.

127
00:18:03,458 --> 00:18:04,937
NED:
Ta-da!

128
00:18:07,178 --> 00:18:12,696
- Are you crazy?
- Wanna see my trick shot? It's better.

129
00:18:13,858 --> 00:18:16,691
I don't believe you!

130
00:18:18,858 --> 00:18:22,373
You know, you're beautiful
when you're angry, sweetheart.

131
00:18:22,538 --> 00:18:23,527
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

132
00:18:23,698 --> 00:18:27,407
You come to help me or scare
me to death? You do that again...

133
00:18:27,578 --> 00:18:31,332
...I'll tack you up on the wall to dry.
- I love that sexy talk!

134
00:18:54,778 --> 00:18:58,407
Hi. I'm going to Camp Crystal Lake.

135
00:19:12,258 --> 00:19:14,692
Guess I always wanted to
work with children.

136
00:19:14,858 --> 00:19:18,851
I hate when people call them "kids."
Sounds like little goats.

137
00:19:19,018 --> 00:19:23,250
But when you've had a dream
as long as I have, you'll do anything.

138
00:19:44,138 --> 00:19:47,972
Hey, wasn't that the road for
Camp Crystal Lake back there?

139
00:19:52,898 --> 00:19:55,173
I think we better stop.

140
00:19:57,658 --> 00:19:59,330
Please?

141
00:20:01,458 --> 00:20:05,656
Stop, please! Please! Stop!

142
00:20:06,178 --> 00:20:08,453
Please, stop!

143
00:20:10,578 --> 00:20:12,808
[SCREAMS]

144
00:20:13,538 --> 00:20:15,608
[TIRES SCREECHING]

145
00:20:23,178 --> 00:20:25,214
[GROANS]

146
00:20:25,498 --> 00:20:27,011
Ow.

147
00:20:27,178 --> 00:20:29,089
[DOOR CLOSES]

148
00:20:30,618 --> 00:20:32,927
Ow.

149
00:21:28,458 --> 00:21:31,575
No. No.

150
00:21:33,698 --> 00:21:34,687
No.

151
00:21:36,218 --> 00:21:37,970
[GASPS]

152
00:21:46,058 --> 00:21:50,210
NED: All right, move it out.
A little to the left. Little to the left.

153
00:21:54,178 --> 00:21:59,650
Move it out. Move it out. Okay,
little to the left. Now... No, no.

154
00:22:00,378 --> 00:22:04,053
Let's go. Okay. Okay. Good. Good.

155
00:22:15,658 --> 00:22:19,128
If you were a flavor of ice cream,
what would it be?

156
00:22:19,298 --> 00:22:23,086
- Rocky Road.
NED: Hey!

157
00:22:35,658 --> 00:22:38,491
What's that vitamin C
stuff do for you, anyway?

158
00:22:38,658 --> 00:22:42,697
Vitamin C is supposed to neutralize
the nitrates or something.

159
00:22:43,538 --> 00:22:46,848
MARCIE: What's the matter?
Do you see something?

160
00:22:49,698 --> 00:22:51,973
BRENDA:
No. Nothing.

161
00:22:53,138 --> 00:22:54,969
[SCREAMS]

162
00:22:55,258 --> 00:22:59,297
Ned! Get out of here!

163
00:22:59,458 --> 00:23:01,892
[BRENDA AND NED GIGGLING]

164
00:23:07,018 --> 00:23:10,727
MARCIE: Ready to go back to work?
BILL: Yeah.

165
00:23:14,058 --> 00:23:17,607
- Come on, Alice.
- Help! Help!

166
00:23:17,818 --> 00:23:22,846
- Something's wrong with Ned.
JACK: Get a life preserver!

167
00:23:33,018 --> 00:23:34,531
Help!

168
00:23:38,738 --> 00:23:40,933
JACK: Can he swim?
MARCIE: I don't know.

169
00:23:41,098 --> 00:23:43,817
- He's right around here somewhere.
JACK: I got it.

170
00:23:43,978 --> 00:23:46,287
Go ahead, dive for him.

171
00:23:48,058 --> 00:23:49,969
MARCIE: There he is!
BRENDA: Help me.

172
00:23:50,138 --> 00:23:52,015
MARCIE:
Watch his head.

173
00:23:53,378 --> 00:23:55,687
- Careful.
ALICE: Okay.

174
00:23:57,898 --> 00:24:00,776
MARCIE: Watch his head!
ALICE: Got him?

175
00:24:06,858 --> 00:24:10,214
- Can you give mouth-to-mouth?
BRENDA: Yeah.

176
00:24:14,858 --> 00:24:17,736
MARCIE: Oh, God.
- Come on, Ned.

177
00:24:18,378 --> 00:24:20,846
MARCIE: Oh, Neddy!
- Oh, Jesus Christ!

178
00:24:21,138 --> 00:24:23,254
[YELLING]

179
00:24:26,218 --> 00:24:30,530
NED:
Look, I'm sorry. I'm sorry, all right?

180
00:24:55,658 --> 00:24:56,886
[SCREAMS]

181
00:25:01,858 --> 00:25:03,496
ALICE:
Bill!

182
00:25:03,658 --> 00:25:08,129
Bill, come here, quick! Hurry!

183
00:25:11,698 --> 00:25:15,247
BILL: What is it?
- There's a snake over there.

184
00:25:15,418 --> 00:25:17,090
BILL:
Where?

185
00:25:23,738 --> 00:25:26,536
- What do I do?
- Kill it.

186
00:25:26,698 --> 00:25:28,017
It might bite.

187
00:25:28,178 --> 00:25:31,807
- Haven't you ever been in the woods?
- We're not in the woods.

188
00:25:31,978 --> 00:25:34,048
- Bill, what are you doing?
- There's a snake.

189
00:25:34,218 --> 00:25:36,607
- Why are we in here?
NED: Feet don't fail me now!

190
00:25:36,778 --> 00:25:38,609
- There it is!
NED: Oh, God!

191
00:25:40,778 --> 00:25:42,336
I can't sleep with a snake in here.

192
00:25:42,498 --> 00:25:44,375
BRENDA:
Nobody said anything about snakes.

193
00:25:44,538 --> 00:25:48,213
- Kill it!
- I can't get it until it comes out.

194
00:25:48,378 --> 00:25:51,336
- Well, call him!
- How do you call a snake?

195
00:25:51,498 --> 00:25:53,295
JACK:
I'll flush him!

196
00:25:55,458 --> 00:25:58,416
[WOMEN SCREAMING]

197
00:25:58,658 --> 00:26:00,614
BILL: I got it.
ALICE: Where...?

198
00:26:00,778 --> 00:26:03,338
NED:
Look out! I got him!

199
00:26:03,578 --> 00:26:05,136
[SCREAMING]

200
00:26:07,138 --> 00:26:08,810
BRENDA:
Oh, God.

201
00:26:13,018 --> 00:26:15,168
Is it dead?

202
00:26:15,338 --> 00:26:18,648
Either that or it's got a very short clone.

203
00:26:19,698 --> 00:26:23,930
- At least we know what's for dinner.
- Marcie!

204
00:26:24,098 --> 00:26:25,531
BILL:
Gross.

205
00:26:28,778 --> 00:26:31,451
BRENDA: I'm making salad. Want me
to make some for everybody?

206
00:26:31,618 --> 00:26:35,008
- That'd be great. There's hamburger...
- None for me.

207
00:26:35,178 --> 00:26:37,487
There are apples.
Know how to make apple pie?

208
00:26:37,658 --> 00:26:41,333
- Sure. No sweat.
BRENDA: What is going on?

209
00:26:50,218 --> 00:26:52,209
Oh, shit.

210
00:26:54,138 --> 00:26:57,892
- Who are you people?
- Camp counselors. Ned is fooling around.

211
00:26:58,058 --> 00:26:59,855
NED: Right, just...
- Can it, Cochise.

212
00:27:00,018 --> 00:27:02,327
Steve Christy hire you people?
He pay you for this?

213
00:27:02,498 --> 00:27:04,614
JACK: Nice bike.
- You been smoking, boy?

214
00:27:04,778 --> 00:27:07,338
Smoking? Don't smoke. Causes cancer.

215
00:27:07,498 --> 00:27:12,526
You get off a spaceship or something?
Colombian gold. Grass. Hash. The weed.

216
00:27:12,698 --> 00:27:14,689
NED: What's he talking about?
- Don't get smart.

217
00:27:14,858 --> 00:27:19,295
NED: Me? I'm as dumb as they come.
- Not another word, understand?

218
00:27:19,458 --> 00:27:22,894
Nothing's going on here.
We're getting the place in shape.

219
00:27:23,058 --> 00:27:24,047
DORF:
For what?

220
00:27:24,218 --> 00:27:27,688
- Is there anything we can do to help?
- I'm looking for somebody.

221
00:27:27,858 --> 00:27:31,612
BILL: Who's that?
- A guy named Ralph. The town crazy.

222
00:27:31,778 --> 00:27:34,451
There's no crazy people around here.

223
00:27:34,618 --> 00:27:39,533
DORF: I told you to sit on it. I got word
Ralph was pedaling out this way...

224
00:27:39,738 --> 00:27:42,855
...spouting his gospel.
- We haven't seen anybody here.

225
00:27:43,018 --> 00:27:45,896
- Just us.
- This guy Ralph. Is he dangerous?

226
00:27:46,498 --> 00:27:49,092
Every time that loony gets drunk,
he gets his calling.

227
00:27:49,258 --> 00:27:52,728
I spend the morning in court,
he gets a week in jail.

228
00:27:52,898 --> 00:27:56,937
MAN OVER RADIO: <i>Cycle Two,</i>
<i>where are you? Come in, Cycle Two.</i>

229
00:27:57,098 --> 00:28:00,454
This is Dorf. I'm out here
at Camp Crystal Lake. Over.

230
00:28:00,618 --> 00:28:03,815
<i>Haul it back in, Dorf.</i>
<i>Chief wants you back in town.</i>

231
00:28:03,978 --> 00:28:06,697
Roger that. 10-4. On my way. Out.

232
00:28:08,458 --> 00:28:10,847
Never keep the chief waiting.

233
00:28:13,018 --> 00:28:18,251
You kids keep your noses clean.
You'll be hearing from me if you don't.

234
00:28:21,378 --> 00:28:24,176
We ain't gonna stand
for no weirdness out here.

235
00:29:07,178 --> 00:29:12,935
I'm a messenger of God.
You're doomed if you stay here.

236
00:29:14,858 --> 00:29:18,373
This place is cursed. Cursed.

237
00:29:19,858 --> 00:29:23,168
- It's got a death curse!
- Who are you?

238
00:29:23,338 --> 00:29:25,294
What do you want?

239
00:29:25,458 --> 00:29:29,656
- God sent me.
- Get out of here, man!

240
00:29:29,818 --> 00:29:34,494
I got to warn you.
You're doomed if you stay.

241
00:29:34,658 --> 00:29:38,890
Go. Go!

242
00:29:49,578 --> 00:29:54,015
- I think we just met Ralph.
- God, what's next?

243
00:30:03,738 --> 00:30:08,528
You're doomed. You're all doomed.

244
00:30:32,698 --> 00:30:34,131
- Who likes them rare?
- Me.

245
00:30:34,298 --> 00:30:37,495
BRENDA: How can you guys eat that?
It looks like dead animals.

246
00:30:37,658 --> 00:30:41,094
Dead animals? That's the old counselors.
You cannibals!

247
00:30:41,258 --> 00:30:44,216
If you'd mix this stuff right,
you'd get all the protein you need.

248
00:30:44,378 --> 00:30:47,450
BILL: Too bad Annie never showed.
She was supposed to be a good cook.

249
00:30:47,618 --> 00:30:50,974
MARCIE: Don't expect me to play chef.
NED: The squaws are revolting.

250
00:30:51,138 --> 00:30:53,891
- Trouble?
- Yeah. A bad bulb or no power.

251
00:30:54,058 --> 00:30:56,128
Seems a little gloomy in here.

252
00:30:56,298 --> 00:30:58,687
Steve taught me how to use
the emergency generator.

253
00:30:58,858 --> 00:31:02,248
- Town power lines are lousy.
NED: Don't you love that macho talk?

254
00:31:02,458 --> 00:31:04,414
Emergency generator.

255
00:31:04,578 --> 00:31:06,455
JACK: Want to give me a hand?
BILL: Yeah.

256
00:31:06,618 --> 00:31:09,052
BRENDA: Wait for me.
JACK: Can you watch the burgers?

257
00:31:09,218 --> 00:31:12,096
NED: Sure.
BRENDA: Burn them.

258
00:31:15,498 --> 00:31:19,207
- Think he's gonna be bent out of shape?
JACK: I don't know.

259
00:31:19,378 --> 00:31:23,132
This looks almost like the one
at my uncle's cabin in Maine.

260
00:31:23,298 --> 00:31:26,688
JACK: Well, here goes.
BRENDA: What an antique.

261
00:31:27,818 --> 00:31:30,810
[GENERATOR STARTS]

262
00:31:34,538 --> 00:31:37,371
Well, what hath God wrought?

263
00:31:59,898 --> 00:32:01,456
[NED HUMMING]

264
00:32:01,618 --> 00:32:02,687
MARCIE:
No.

265
00:32:34,178 --> 00:32:37,215
[WHISTLING]

266
00:32:47,458 --> 00:32:49,255
[CREAKING]

267
00:32:50,978 --> 00:32:52,696
NED:
Hello?

268
00:33:01,698 --> 00:33:03,768
Can I help you?

269
00:33:09,738 --> 00:33:13,094
Hello? Hello?

270
00:33:14,538 --> 00:33:17,416
MARCIE: Come on.
JACK: Coming, I'm coming.

271
00:33:20,578 --> 00:33:24,571
Wind's come up.
Shifted a good 180 degrees.

272
00:33:24,738 --> 00:33:27,571
MARCIE:
Makes me want to hold onto you.

273
00:33:31,258 --> 00:33:34,853
- What about Ned?
- I don't love Ned.

274
00:33:35,018 --> 00:33:38,090
- He keeps acting like such a jerk.
- Neddy!

275
00:33:38,258 --> 00:33:40,977
- Don't call him.
- Thought you wanted to give him...

276
00:33:41,138 --> 00:33:42,935
...one of your motherly lectures.

277
00:33:43,098 --> 00:33:45,931
Look, Neddy's gonna do whatever
Neddy wants to do, you know?

278
00:33:46,098 --> 00:33:47,497
[THUNDERING]

279
00:33:47,658 --> 00:33:52,095
It's gonna storm. Gonna tear down
that valley like a son of a gun.

280
00:33:52,258 --> 00:33:54,692
I've been afraid of storms
since I was little.

281
00:33:54,858 --> 00:33:57,053
No. Really?

282
00:33:57,218 --> 00:34:01,177
I've had this dream about five or six
times where I'm in a thunderstorm...

283
00:34:01,338 --> 00:34:02,532
Uh-huh.

284
00:34:02,698 --> 00:34:08,773
...and it's raining really hard. It sounds
like pebbles when it hits the ground.

285
00:34:08,938 --> 00:34:14,535
I hear it and I try to block it out
with my hands, only it doesn't work.

286
00:34:14,698 --> 00:34:17,576
It just keeps getting
louder and louder.

287
00:34:18,578 --> 00:34:23,333
And then the rain turns to blood...

288
00:34:24,018 --> 00:34:28,614
...and the blood washes away
in little rivers...

289
00:34:29,778 --> 00:34:32,929
...and then the sound stops.

290
00:34:34,338 --> 00:34:40,129
- It's just a dream.
- I know. I call it my "shower dream."

291
00:34:40,418 --> 00:34:44,775
Hey, hey. This is no dream.
Come on, we're gonna get soaked.

292
00:35:41,378 --> 00:35:43,175
MARCIE:
Wow.

293
00:36:40,138 --> 00:36:42,857
Jack and Marcie are gonna get drenched!

294
00:36:43,018 --> 00:36:45,452
BILL:
Not if they're where I think they are.

295
00:37:10,298 --> 00:37:11,413
That's nice.

296
00:37:11,578 --> 00:37:15,617
I know what we can do.
We'll play Monopoly.

297
00:37:15,778 --> 00:37:18,850
- I hate Monopoly!
BRENDA: Not the way I play it.

298
00:37:19,018 --> 00:37:22,055
- Like what?
- We're going to play strip Monopoly.

299
00:37:22,218 --> 00:37:26,416
- I'll be the shoe.
- You have got to be kidding.

300
00:37:26,578 --> 00:37:28,091
What if Steve walks in?

301
00:37:28,258 --> 00:37:32,490
We'll give him a handicap.
He can keep his boots on. It's easy.

302
00:37:32,658 --> 00:37:37,971
Instead of rent, you pay clothes. Bill
can be banker. Unless he's chicken.

303
00:37:38,138 --> 00:37:40,698
Heaven help you if you land
in my hotel!

304
00:37:40,858 --> 00:37:44,134
BRENDA: Why don't you see if Marcie
left any of that grass?

305
00:37:44,698 --> 00:37:48,452
BILL: What happened to my 500's?
- They're there. Where's my shoe?

306
00:37:48,698 --> 00:37:51,053
[MARCIE MOANING]

307
00:38:57,258 --> 00:39:00,170
I'm not going to pass "Go"
without a glow.

308
00:39:00,338 --> 00:39:03,011
We rolled for you. You're going last.

309
00:39:03,178 --> 00:39:06,375
Community Chest cannot
give you your clothes back.

310
00:39:07,298 --> 00:39:10,370
Double sixes! I get to roll again!

311
00:39:10,538 --> 00:39:13,496
- We're being hustled.
- I think you're right.

312
00:39:17,498 --> 00:39:20,092
You are so fine.

313
00:39:26,778 --> 00:39:28,689
Where are you going?

314
00:39:28,858 --> 00:39:31,850
I gotta pee.
You're lying on my bladder.

315
00:39:35,018 --> 00:39:39,614
Hurry back, okay?
It's getting cold in here.

316
00:39:48,178 --> 00:39:51,250
- You'll save my place for me?
- Yeah.

317
00:40:08,458 --> 00:40:09,732
Five.

318
00:40:10,778 --> 00:40:14,896
- Baltic Avenue. I'll buy it.
- No one ever lands on Baltic Avenue.

319
00:40:15,058 --> 00:40:17,094
- I think it's a pretty color.
- Okay.

320
00:40:19,178 --> 00:40:20,657
Come on.

321
00:40:21,578 --> 00:40:23,011
Eight.

322
00:40:24,458 --> 00:40:29,373
- Baltic Avenue. You owe me one boot.
- Coming.

323
00:40:29,538 --> 00:40:31,608
Alice draws first blood.

324
00:40:31,778 --> 00:40:35,487
- Terrible way to talk about my feet.
- Thank you.

325
00:40:35,658 --> 00:40:36,886
Who's next?

326
00:40:38,698 --> 00:40:41,929
You know I think I'm beginning
to like this game.

327
00:40:42,098 --> 00:40:44,931
Wait until he lands
on my old Kentucky home.

328
00:40:45,098 --> 00:40:47,737
- More beer? More beer.
- Let's see. A railroad.

329
00:42:45,151 --> 00:42:49,383
<i>Forty Yards to the Outhouse,</i>
by Willie Makit.

330
00:42:49,951 --> 00:42:53,148
Come on, kids,
you can do better than that.

331
00:42:53,311 --> 00:42:54,426
[DOOR CREAKING]

332
00:42:54,591 --> 00:42:56,104
Jack?

333
00:43:00,991 --> 00:43:02,663
Jack?

334
00:43:06,911 --> 00:43:10,506
Jack? Hmm.

335
00:43:17,031 --> 00:43:21,070
When I looked into that mirror,
I knew I'd always be ugly.

336
00:43:22,111 --> 00:43:26,502
I said,
"Lady, you'll always be plain."

337
00:43:26,671 --> 00:43:28,104
[GIGGLES]

338
00:43:29,271 --> 00:43:30,386
[RUSTLING]

339
00:43:30,551 --> 00:43:31,745
Hello?

340
00:43:51,471 --> 00:43:53,462
Aha!

341
00:43:58,511 --> 00:44:01,184
[HUMMING]

342
00:44:01,351 --> 00:44:03,546
[CLANKING]

343
00:44:07,791 --> 00:44:09,019
Ned?

344
00:44:12,671 --> 00:44:14,901
Hey, come on, you guys.

345
00:44:39,951 --> 00:44:42,067
OIly, olly in free.

346
00:44:57,551 --> 00:44:59,781
It must be my imagination.

347
00:45:18,191 --> 00:45:19,704
BILL: Hello.
- Shit.

348
00:45:19,871 --> 00:45:22,590
BRENDA: Worst run of bad luck
since Richard Nixon.

349
00:45:22,751 --> 00:45:24,503
BILL:
You can call it quits.

350
00:45:24,671 --> 00:45:29,620
Fat chance! You're two steps
from Pacific Avenue and Skin City.

351
00:45:34,031 --> 00:45:35,510
ALICE:
Uh-oh.

352
00:45:35,671 --> 00:45:38,981
What can I say?
It's not much, but I call it home.

353
00:45:39,551 --> 00:45:41,223
[DOOR SLAMS OPEN]

354
00:45:41,391 --> 00:45:42,540
ALICE: Oh, no.
BRENDA: Wait.

355
00:45:42,711 --> 00:45:45,225
- I'll get it. I'll get it.
BRENDA: Get the money.

356
00:45:45,511 --> 00:45:48,344
ALICE: God!
BILL: It's blowing like crazy out there.

357
00:45:48,511 --> 00:45:52,504
I think I left the windows
in my cabin open. Shoot!

358
00:45:54,871 --> 00:45:58,261
We'll have to finish this game
some other night.

359
00:45:58,431 --> 00:46:00,899
Just when it was getting interesting.

360
00:46:01,631 --> 00:46:04,145
- See you guys in the morning.
BILL: See you.

361
00:46:04,311 --> 00:46:06,586
ALICE: Good night.
BRENDA: Good night.

362
00:46:14,511 --> 00:46:16,786
ALICE:
Look at this mess! Here.

363
00:46:16,951 --> 00:46:21,149
- Were you going to go ahead with it?
- I hadn't made up my mind.

364
00:46:21,311 --> 00:46:24,223
BILL: We'll have to finish
the game another night.

365
00:46:27,111 --> 00:46:28,908
[MUSIC PLAYS]

366
00:46:40,831 --> 00:46:46,224
- Is there anything else you want?
- No, thanks, Sandy. I'm fine.

367
00:46:46,391 --> 00:46:49,463
You can't go out in that rain.
You want to drown?

368
00:46:49,631 --> 00:46:52,782
I've got to.
I've got six new counselors at camp.

369
00:46:52,951 --> 00:46:56,148
They are babes in the woods,
in every sense.

370
00:46:56,311 --> 00:47:00,702
They'll be okay if they know enough
to come out of the rain.

371
00:47:00,871 --> 00:47:05,183
- Well, what do I owe you?
- Just a night on the town, Steve.

372
00:47:05,351 --> 00:47:10,061
- Come on now, you know what I mean.
- That's okay. Two and a quarter.

373
00:47:13,151 --> 00:47:14,630
Thank you.

374
00:47:26,671 --> 00:47:29,424
- Here's your change.
- No, you keep it.

375
00:47:29,591 --> 00:47:30,785
- Thank you.
- Sure.

376
00:47:30,951 --> 00:47:32,464
- Drive careful.
- I will.

377
00:47:32,631 --> 00:47:33,620
Good night.

378
00:48:10,231 --> 00:48:12,620
[THUNDERING]

379
00:48:29,551 --> 00:48:31,746
[DOOR CLOSES]

380
00:48:34,591 --> 00:48:37,310
[HUMMING]

381
00:48:56,031 --> 00:48:58,909
[CLANKING]

382
00:49:38,031 --> 00:49:40,784
[CREAKING]

383
00:50:16,391 --> 00:50:17,870
[ENGINE SPUTTERING]

384
00:50:51,111 --> 00:50:52,339
STEVE: Hi.
MAN: Hi.

385
00:50:52,511 --> 00:50:56,345
- Thought that'd go through anything.
- Not dragging a trailer.

386
00:50:56,511 --> 00:50:57,944
- Can you give me a lift?
- Yeah.

387
00:50:58,111 --> 00:51:02,070
- I'll have a counselor bring me back.
- Why not?

388
00:52:19,311 --> 00:52:21,108
GIRL:
Help me!

389
00:52:44,951 --> 00:52:46,987
Help me!

390
00:53:13,711 --> 00:53:15,064
Hello.

391
00:53:18,751 --> 00:53:24,189
- Hello.
GIRL: Here. Please somebody help me.

392
00:53:24,351 --> 00:53:25,625
BRENDA:
Hello.

393
00:53:28,871 --> 00:53:30,145
Hello.

394
00:53:33,991 --> 00:53:35,265
Hello.

395
00:53:40,551 --> 00:53:41,779
Hello?

396
00:53:47,191 --> 00:53:52,629
GIRL: Come quickly, please.
Come quickly. Help.

397
00:54:05,791 --> 00:54:08,988
BRENDA:
Where are you? Hello.

398
00:54:28,071 --> 00:54:29,299
Hello?

399
00:54:35,551 --> 00:54:36,745
All right.

400
00:54:38,991 --> 00:54:41,664
Come on out! You're not funny anymore!

401
00:54:43,551 --> 00:54:45,462
It's not funny at all.

402
00:54:57,831 --> 00:55:00,391
[SCREAMING]

403
00:55:43,191 --> 00:55:44,624
[DOOR OPENS]

404
00:55:47,631 --> 00:55:48,859
Bill.

405
00:55:50,151 --> 00:55:54,349
- Hi. The generator is okay.
- I thought I heard a scream.

406
00:55:54,511 --> 00:55:58,345
- How can you hear in that wind?
- It sounded like Brenda.

407
00:55:58,511 --> 00:55:59,785
I'd better look.

408
00:55:59,951 --> 00:56:02,624
Somebody turned on the lights
at the archery range.

409
00:56:02,791 --> 00:56:03,826
BILL:
What?

410
00:56:05,551 --> 00:56:07,269
I can't see anything.

411
00:56:08,111 --> 00:56:09,942
ALICE:
They're off now.

412
00:56:10,831 --> 00:56:12,822
I'm gonna check it out.

413
00:56:13,311 --> 00:56:17,589
- Bill. Can I come?
- Come on.

414
00:56:20,751 --> 00:56:22,104
ALICE:
Brenda!

415
00:56:22,791 --> 00:56:24,383
Brenda!

416
00:56:29,471 --> 00:56:31,143
Where is she?

417
00:56:32,831 --> 00:56:35,425
She must be with Jack and Marcie.

418
00:56:38,391 --> 00:56:40,188
BILL: Alice?
- Yeah?

419
00:56:40,351 --> 00:56:41,625
Come here.

420
00:57:00,351 --> 00:57:03,343
What is going on?

421
00:57:06,751 --> 00:57:07,979
Come on!

422
00:57:14,151 --> 00:57:16,267
ALICE: Jack.
BILL: Jack.

423
00:57:16,431 --> 00:57:18,023
ALICE:
Jack, open the door.

424
00:57:20,551 --> 00:57:25,545
- Where are they?
- I don't know. Come on.

425
00:57:28,031 --> 00:57:29,020
[KNOCKING]

426
00:57:29,191 --> 00:57:30,419
ALICE:
Brenda?

427
00:57:31,551 --> 00:57:32,950
Marcie?

428
00:57:34,151 --> 00:57:38,827
Jack? Neddy?

429
00:57:43,191 --> 00:57:45,785
Bill, I think we should call someone.

430
00:57:46,391 --> 00:57:48,586
If this is a joke, I'll brain them!

431
00:57:48,751 --> 00:57:53,302
I'm serious.
I really think we should call someone.

432
00:58:01,471 --> 00:58:03,223
BILL:
The sucker's locked.

433
00:58:03,391 --> 00:58:05,347
- Where's the key?
ALICE: I don't know.

434
00:58:05,511 --> 00:58:06,990
Wait a minute.

435
00:58:15,671 --> 00:58:17,309
Watch out.

436
00:58:21,751 --> 00:58:23,150
BILL:
Be careful.

437
00:58:25,151 --> 00:58:26,709
Let me get the light.

438
00:58:34,391 --> 00:58:35,983
ALICE:
What's wrong?

439
00:58:36,471 --> 00:58:38,905
BILL:
It's dead. Try the pay phone.

440
00:58:39,071 --> 00:58:41,301
ALICE:
Do you have a dime or a quarter?

441
00:58:41,791 --> 00:58:43,543
BILL:
No. Check the desk.

442
00:58:50,431 --> 00:58:51,420
[CLICKING]

443
00:58:51,591 --> 00:58:53,104
ALICE:
Hello?

444
00:58:53,631 --> 00:58:55,781
This damn thing's dead too!

445
00:58:56,071 --> 00:58:57,584
[ENGINE SPUTTERING]

446
00:59:10,711 --> 00:59:12,667
What's the matter with it?

447
00:59:12,831 --> 00:59:14,230
It's wet.

448
00:59:14,391 --> 00:59:15,380
I don't know.

449
00:59:15,551 --> 00:59:19,100
Why don't we just hike out of here?
Get out. Right now!

450
00:59:19,271 --> 00:59:22,741
It's 10 miles to the nearest crossroads.
Steve will be back soon.

451
00:59:22,911 --> 00:59:26,108
We can use his jeep if we need
to get help. Don't worry.

452
00:59:26,271 --> 00:59:29,786
- There's some stupid explanation.
- Like what?

453
00:59:29,951 --> 00:59:33,546
We'll be laughing about this tomorrow,
I promise.

454
00:59:36,871 --> 00:59:38,350
Let's get out of the rain.

455
00:59:43,231 --> 00:59:47,941
TIERNEY: It's not bad enough to have
Friday the 13th, we have a full moon.

456
00:59:48,111 --> 00:59:52,707
We keep statistics. We have more
accidents, more rapes, more robberies...

457
00:59:52,871 --> 00:59:56,466
...more homicides, more of everything
when there's a full moon.

458
00:59:56,631 --> 00:59:59,225
- It upsets people. Makes them nuts.
- Ah.

459
00:59:59,391 --> 01:00:02,064
You're making science
out of coincidence.

460
01:00:03,831 --> 01:00:06,584
I hear Ralph was out your way today.

461
01:00:06,751 --> 01:00:09,345
His wife was a nervous wreck
until we got him home.

462
01:00:09,511 --> 01:00:13,060
That's all I need,
Crazy Ralph running around.

463
01:00:13,231 --> 01:00:15,426
Well, the rain's stopping.

464
01:00:16,431 --> 01:00:18,183
It was a pisser while it lasted.

465
01:00:18,351 --> 01:00:21,900
WOMAN: <i>Sgt. Tierney, come in.</i>
<i>Sgt. Tierney, Car Niner.</i>

466
01:00:22,991 --> 01:00:24,310
This is Tierney.

467
01:00:24,471 --> 01:00:29,147
<i>Rescue squad with Jaws of Life.</i>
<i>Near mile-marker 17. Possible fatals.</i>

468
01:00:29,311 --> 01:00:31,620
<i>Three, maybe more, trapped.</i>
<i>Head on.</i>

469
01:00:31,791 --> 01:00:35,909
Roger. Acknowledge receipt.
Estimate arrival, 15 minutes.

470
01:00:45,311 --> 01:00:48,189
- I have to let you off here.
STEVE: Sure.

471
01:00:49,151 --> 01:00:50,345
Thanks.

472
01:00:50,511 --> 01:00:52,183
Good luck.

473
01:00:56,951 --> 01:00:59,021
[SIREN WAILS]

474
01:01:28,551 --> 01:01:31,145
Hello? Who is that?

475
01:01:34,911 --> 01:01:38,347
What are you doing
out in this mess?

476
01:02:11,671 --> 01:02:13,150
[GENERATOR STOPS]

477
01:02:56,671 --> 01:02:58,741
ALICE:
What do you think happened?

478
01:02:59,071 --> 01:03:00,789
BILL:
I don't know.

479
01:03:02,031 --> 01:03:04,670
The generator's probably out of gas.

480
01:03:04,871 --> 01:03:06,782
I'll go check it.

481
01:03:07,951 --> 01:03:10,146
ALICE:
Do you want me to come with you?

482
01:03:10,991 --> 01:03:13,983
Why don't you stay here
and try and sleep.

483
01:03:15,071 --> 01:03:16,345
I'll be right back.

484
01:04:12,751 --> 01:04:14,901
[SQUEAKING]

485
01:04:43,431 --> 01:04:44,784
Full of gas.

486
01:05:17,911 --> 01:05:19,708
[SCREAMS]

487
01:05:27,911 --> 01:05:29,867
Generator.

488
01:07:26,271 --> 01:07:28,341
ALICE:
Bill!

489
01:07:30,151 --> 01:07:32,460
Bill.

490
01:07:33,271 --> 01:07:35,307
Bill.

491
01:07:37,031 --> 01:07:39,101
Bill.

492
01:07:39,431 --> 01:07:41,342
Bill?

493
01:07:44,631 --> 01:07:48,749
Bill. Bill?

494
01:08:00,151 --> 01:08:02,221
Bill.

495
01:08:05,151 --> 01:08:07,142
Bill!

496
01:08:22,711 --> 01:08:25,350
Oh, my God!

497
01:08:25,511 --> 01:08:27,422
[SCREAMING]

498
01:08:36,391 --> 01:08:38,382
[SOBBING]

499
01:09:07,071 --> 01:09:10,905
Oh, my God.

500
01:09:40,311 --> 01:09:43,348
[WHIMPERING]

501
01:11:12,431 --> 01:11:15,468
[RUSTLING]

502
01:11:22,071 --> 01:11:24,585
What am I gonna do?

503
01:11:25,151 --> 01:11:26,982
[SCREAMS]

504
01:11:50,231 --> 01:11:52,699
God!

505
01:11:56,191 --> 01:12:00,343
Oh, God!

506
01:12:03,631 --> 01:12:06,270
Oh, my God.

507
01:12:19,391 --> 01:12:22,940
Steve. Oh, Steve!

508
01:12:33,471 --> 01:12:35,701
Please! Oh, please!

509
01:12:38,951 --> 01:12:40,225
Who are you?

510
01:12:40,991 --> 01:12:44,381
I'm Mrs. Voorhees.
An old friend of the Christys.

511
01:12:44,791 --> 01:12:47,021
Oh. I'm so glad!

512
01:12:47,191 --> 01:12:49,022
VOORHEES:
No, no. There, there.

513
01:12:49,191 --> 01:12:51,751
I can't help you
if you don't calm down.

514
01:12:51,911 --> 01:12:56,507
But she's dead and he's dead.
Oh, my God! Poor Bill! Oh, God!

515
01:12:56,671 --> 01:12:59,868
- All right. Come on, dear. Show me.
- No. No!

516
01:13:00,031 --> 01:13:04,263
It's all right. I'll take care of you.
I used to work for the Christys.

517
01:13:04,431 --> 01:13:07,389
What's going on?
Help me get out of here!

518
01:13:07,551 --> 01:13:10,668
It's this place and the storm.
That's why you're upset.

519
01:13:10,831 --> 01:13:13,982
No, no! They're all dead!
They're all dead!

520
01:13:14,151 --> 01:13:17,029
- All right. I'll go look.
- Don't leave me!

521
01:13:17,191 --> 01:13:21,184
- They'll kill you too!
- I'm not afraid.

522
01:13:38,471 --> 01:13:41,588
Oh, my Lord!

523
01:13:42,551 --> 01:13:44,507
So young.

524
01:13:44,711 --> 01:13:46,269
So pretty.

525
01:13:47,271 --> 01:13:49,307
What monster could have done this?

526
01:13:50,671 --> 01:13:52,821
Bill is out there!

527
01:13:53,591 --> 01:13:56,469
Oh, God, this place!

528
01:13:56,871 --> 01:13:59,863
Steve should never have
opened this place again!

529
01:14:00,031 --> 01:14:02,499
There's been too much trouble here.

530
01:14:03,311 --> 01:14:05,541
Did you know a young boy drowned?

531
01:14:05,711 --> 01:14:08,225
The year before those two others
were killed.

532
01:14:08,391 --> 01:14:10,746
The counselors weren't paying attention!

533
01:14:10,911 --> 01:14:14,460
They were making love
while that young boy drowned!

534
01:14:15,671 --> 01:14:17,946
His name was Jason.

535
01:14:19,511 --> 01:14:22,787
I was working the day it happened.
Preparing meals.

536
01:14:22,951 --> 01:14:25,385
Here. I was the cook.

537
01:14:25,551 --> 01:14:28,543
Jason should have been watched!
Every minute!

538
01:14:28,711 --> 01:14:30,303
He was...

539
01:14:33,191 --> 01:14:35,864
He wasn't a very good swimmer.

540
01:14:37,871 --> 01:14:40,339
We can go now, dear.

541
01:14:40,631 --> 01:14:43,748
I think we should wait for Mr. Christy.

542
01:14:43,911 --> 01:14:45,947
That's not necessary.

543
01:14:46,111 --> 01:14:47,863
I don't understand.

544
01:14:48,911 --> 01:14:50,742
BO Y:
Help me!

545
01:14:50,911 --> 01:14:52,185
Help!

546
01:14:52,351 --> 01:14:53,579
Help, Mommy!

547
01:14:53,751 --> 01:14:56,663
Help! Help, Mommy!

548
01:14:57,591 --> 01:14:59,707
I am, Jason.

549
01:14:59,991 --> 01:15:03,461
- I am.
ALICE: Oh, God.

550
01:15:03,991 --> 01:15:06,824
You see, Jason was my son.

551
01:15:06,991 --> 01:15:09,459
And today is his birthday.

552
01:15:09,631 --> 01:15:12,020
Where's Mr. Christy?

553
01:15:12,191 --> 01:15:15,069
I couldn't let them open this place again.

554
01:15:15,231 --> 01:15:16,789
Could I?

555
01:15:17,391 --> 01:15:19,461
Not after what happened.

556
01:15:23,111 --> 01:15:26,660
Oh, my sweet, innocent Jason.

557
01:15:27,591 --> 01:15:29,866
My only child.

558
01:15:30,391 --> 01:15:31,506
Jason.

559
01:15:36,151 --> 01:15:37,743
You let him drown!

560
01:15:37,911 --> 01:15:40,869
You never paid any attention!

561
01:15:41,031 --> 01:15:43,864
Look what you did to him!

562
01:15:44,031 --> 01:15:48,070
- No.
- Look what you did to him!

563
01:16:47,311 --> 01:16:50,428
IN CHILD'S VOICE:
Kill her, Mommy. Kill her!

564
01:16:54,151 --> 01:16:58,030
Don't let her get away, Mommy.
Don't let her live!

565
01:16:58,191 --> 01:17:02,104
I won't, Jason. I won't!

566
01:17:37,071 --> 01:17:39,949
[GENERATOR STARTS]

567
01:17:49,351 --> 01:17:51,501
ALICE:
Where are the goddamn bullets?

568
01:18:06,991 --> 01:18:08,106
Come, dear.

569
01:18:08,551 --> 01:18:12,624
It will be easier for you
than it was for Jason.

570
01:18:15,551 --> 01:18:19,146
IN CHILD'S VOICE:
Kill her, Mommy. Kill her!

571
01:18:21,111 --> 01:18:22,180
Kill her.

572
01:18:22,351 --> 01:18:24,103
Ah!

573
01:19:55,511 --> 01:19:58,344
VOORHEES IN CHILD'S VOICE:
Kill her, Mommy. Kill her.

574
01:19:58,591 --> 01:20:02,106
She can't hide.
No place to hide.

575
01:20:02,271 --> 01:20:05,024
Get her, Mommy. Get her!

576
01:20:05,191 --> 01:20:07,421
Kill her! Kill her.

577
01:21:09,551 --> 01:21:11,781
[BANGING]

578
01:21:13,671 --> 01:21:15,901
[GLASS SHATTERS]

579
01:21:37,911 --> 01:21:41,347
[DOOR SQUEAKING]

580
01:22:36,711 --> 01:22:37,905
[VOORHEES SCREAMS]

581
01:23:03,671 --> 01:23:05,343
[DOOR SQUEAKS]

582
01:24:01,511 --> 01:24:03,149
[ALICE SCREAMS]

583
01:24:26,671 --> 01:24:28,662
ALICE:
Get off me!

584
01:27:26,671 --> 01:27:29,708
- No. No!
- It's all right, dear. You're okay.

585
01:27:29,871 --> 01:27:32,146
MAN: Ten milligrams, Valium.
It's all right.

586
01:27:32,311 --> 01:27:34,381
It's all over. Everything's over.

587
01:27:37,471 --> 01:27:39,746
Roll over. Roll over, dear.

588
01:27:45,751 --> 01:27:50,029
WOMAN OVER SPEAKER:
<i>Dr. Lewis wanted in surgery.</i>

589
01:27:50,191 --> 01:27:52,751
Okay.

590
01:27:59,391 --> 01:28:01,621
Your folks are on the way up.

591
01:28:04,231 --> 01:28:06,426
Is anyone else alive?

592
01:28:07,831 --> 01:28:09,628
Are they all dead?

593
01:28:10,071 --> 01:28:11,663
Yes, ma'am.

594
01:28:12,551 --> 01:28:17,420
My men pulled you out of the lake.
We thought you were dead too.

595
01:28:18,271 --> 01:28:20,466
Do you remember very much?

596
01:28:20,631 --> 01:28:22,110
The boy.

597
01:28:22,271 --> 01:28:24,227
Is he dead too?

598
01:28:24,471 --> 01:28:27,861
TIERNEY: Who?
- The boy, Jason.

599
01:28:29,231 --> 01:28:30,266
Jason?

600
01:28:30,431 --> 01:28:35,221
In the lake. The one who attacked me.
The one who pulled me under the water.

601
01:28:36,951 --> 01:28:40,421
Ma'am, we didn't find any boy.

602
01:28:42,111 --> 01:28:43,703
But he...

603
01:28:49,791 --> 01:28:52,385
Then he's still there.

